==English==
===Pronunciation===
*wīn, /waɪn/, /waIn/
*:'''Homophones''': [[whine]] (depends on dialect)

===Noun===
'''wine''' ([[uncountable]] and [[countable]]; plural: [[wines]])

#An alcoholic [[beverage]] made from the fermented juice of [[grape]]s.
#An alcoholic beverage made from the fermented juice of fruits or vegetables other than grapes (''usually preceded by the name of the fruit or vegetable; for example, "dandelion wine"'').
#(''[[uncountable]]'') A dark purplish red [[colour]]; the colour of red wine.

